dialog.text:
Of the One Piece world's mail delivery staff, can the [[Animal Species/Summit War Saga#Carrier Bat|Carrier Bats]] deliver packages too? Do pirate crews exchange mid and end of year gifts with each other? P.N. Boneless Ham

[[File:SBS88 Mail Birds.png|thumb|200px]]
matches: Animal Species/Summit War Saga#Carrier Bat|Carrier Bats

dialog.text: I don't want to see pirates getting along like that. It doesn't happen. Carrier Bats are mainly used as a means of contact by the [[World Government]]. For private letters, one can negotiate with a [[Animal Species#News Coo|News Coo]] to deliver it. There's also a private company called "Small Bird Delivery," but they have a small space and short distance. "Albatross Delivery" does long distance, but there's a lot of things they won't deliver. Mail services outside of the government's just aren't that developed. For deliveries between pirates, it's common to use boats. They don't have addresses either, so parting ways with people is heavier than we can imagine.

qa.summary: Carrier Bats are mainly used by the World Government, while pirates use boats for deliveries and don't exchange gifts with each other.
